OverTheWire Bandit – Level 28 → Level 29 

Level Goal
A git repository is hosted at:
  ssh://bandit28-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org/home/bandit28-git/repo on port 2220.
The password for user bandit28-git is the same as the password for bandit28.

Commands Used
git clone
ls
cat

Steps
SSH into the Bandit server.
Use the password of bandit28 to connect as user bandit28-git:
 ssh bandit28-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org -p 2220
Clone the repository located at /home/bandit28-git/repo:
 git clone ssh://bandit28-git@bandit.labs.overthewire.org:2220/home/bandit28-git/repo
Navigate into the cloned repository directory:
 cd repo
List and inspect files to locate the password for bandit29:
 ls -la
 cat <file-containing-password>

Result
Successfully retrieved the password for bandit29 from the cloned git repository.

What I Learned
Accessing remote git repositories over SSH with non-default ports.
Using git clone to explore remote repos.
Searching for sensitive information inside git repositories during CTF challenges
